    "(10)We further define the total quasi-momentum distribution asn k (t) = σ=↑,↓ n k,σ (t).",
    "(11)From the quasi-momentum distribution, we obtain the kinetic energy of the conduction electron:E kin (t) = k ε k n k (t).",
    "(12)The final observable of interest is the correlator between the electronic spin density on site i and the localized spin on site i:S cf,i = ⟨ Ŝc,i • Ŝf,i ⟩.",
    "(13)Often, we will calculate the total correlation by summing over all sites:S cf = L i=1 S cf,i.",
    "(14)This accounts for the decreasing filling as L increases in the case of a single charge carrier."
